label: Measure
description:
Grouping of dental services utilized: 
Annual Dental Visit (D0100 - D9999 or Safety Net Clinics (SNC) 03 Encounters CY 2013-2019). For CY 2019, Annual Dental Visit also included CPT 99188 along with CDT procedures and SNC 03 encounters.
For each measure below, CY 2016, 2017, 2018 and 2019 captured members who received the CDT procedures or SNCs 03 Encounters with identified ICD 10 Codes.
Exams/Oral Health Evaluations (D0120, D0145, or D0150; CY 2016, 2017, 2018 and 2019 included SNCs 03 Encounters with identified ICD 10 Codes ), 
Use of Diagnostic Services (D0100-D0999;  CY 2016, 2017, 2018 and 2019 included SNCs 03 Encounters with identified ICD 10 Codes ),
Use of Dental Treatment Services (D2000 - D9999; CY 2016, 2017, 2018 and 2019 included SNCs 03 Encounters with identified ICD 10 Codes ), 
Use of Preventative Services (D1000-D1999; CY 2016, 2017 , 2018 and 2019 included SNCs 03 Encounters with identified ICD 10 Codes ). For CY 2019, Use of Preventive Services also included CPT 99188 along with CDT procedures and SNC 03 encounters, 
Use of Restorative Services (D2000-D2999; CY 2016, 2017, 2018 and 2019 included SNCs 03 Encounters with identified ICD 10 Codes ), 
Treatment/Prevention for Caries (D2000-D2999) or Caries-Preventive Procedure (D1203-D1208, D1310, D1330, D1351; CY 2016, 2017 , 2018 and 2019 included SNCs 03 Encounters with identified ICD 10 Codes ), 
Use of Sealants (Number of members ages 6-9 who received a dental sealant (D1351) on a permanent first molar (tooth number = 3, 14, 19, 30) or Number of members ages 10-14 who received a dental sealant (D1351) on a permanent second molar (tooth number=2, 15, 18, 31); CY 2016, 2017, 2018 and 2019 included SNCs 03 Encounters with ICD 10 Code Z98810).

label: Age Group
description: Age Group for Measures: Age <1, Age 1-2, Age 3-5, Age 6-9, Age 10-14, Age 15-18, Age 19-20, Age 21-34, Age 35-44, Age 45-64, Age 65-74, Age 75+

label: Users Annotation code
Users Annotation Description
Utilization %
description: Percentage of members in that measure with respect to the number of eligible members (3 months continuous enrollment in the same plan) within the measurement period.
